SUMMARY:Notes From Underground
LOCATION:The Players’ Guild of Hamilton\, 80 Queen St S\, Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: A Drama Studio (Mississauga\, ON)\nContent warnings: S
 exual Content\, Coarse Language\, Violence\nGenre: Theatre—Drama\nThe Un
 derground Man has spent the past 20 years living in a squalid corner of St
 . Petersburg in bitter\, self-imposed isolation. Join him as he grapples w
 ith something terrible he did on a dirty\, snowy\, night 15 years ago... P
 erformed by a cast of 7\, this adaptation of Dostoevsky’s classic invite
 s you to consider: what's the price of arrogance? Can you accept love if y
 ou're a tyrant? What is the way out of “the Underground”?\nGeneral Adm
 ission: $14\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/events/notes-from-underground/
URL:https://hftco.ca/events/notes-from-underground/
STATUS:CONFIRMED
