SUMMARY:For What We Labour
LOCATION:The St. Luke's Mission\, 454 John St N (enter at Macauley St E)\, 
 Hamilton\, ON
DESCRIPTION:Company: Hiccup Productions (Hamilton\, ON)\nContent warnings: 
 Sexual Content\, Coarse Language\nGenre: Theatre—Comedy\nThis farce take
 s place in Ancient Greece\, in the House of the Elliminestai. The daughter
  of the house is pregnant (gasp!) and her attempt to escape her inherited 
 duty is foiled (groan) by the return of the baby daddy (tenterhooks). This
  original tale is narrated by an expelled member of The Greek Chorus. What
  can go wrong? Watch as The House dissolves into chaos and hijinx\, leavin
 g the housekeeper... to clean up the mess.\nGeneral Admission: $14\nMore i
 nfo: https://hftco.ca/events/for-what-we-labour/
