DESCRIPTION:Company: Morbidelli 17 Productions (Los Angeles\, CA)\nContent 
 warnings: Coarse Language\nGenre: Theatre—Comedy\, Storytelling/Solo Sho
 w\nPublic displays of affection! Mass shootings! Drugs\, deities - it's th
 e first day of class\, and Prof. G. explains why you can't send naughty ph
 otos to your classmates and why it's important to out-run the criminology 
 students. In this original one-act performance\, you're a student again\, 
 and Prof. G presents his survival guide for community college. A dark come
 dy about social interaction\, education\, mass media and why it's importan
 t to sit next to someone who is sexually unattractive to you - your future
  may depend on it.\nGeneral Admission: $14\nMore info: https://hftco.ca/ev
 ents/the-syllabus/
